Business Brief -- Citicorp:
   Sale of Rest of Ambac Inc.
   Raises About $550 Million
Currently, the bank's equity, or tier one ratio, stands at
3.7%, below the minimum regulatory requirement of 4% that
goes into effect at year end.
   Late Wednesday, Citicorp said that it sold its remaining
17.4 million shares at $31.75 each through underwriters led
by Morgan Stanley  Co. That's well above the $20 a share the
bank received when it sold a 50.3% stake last summer. In New
York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Citicorp
closed at $17.12, up 37.5 cents. Ambac, also listed on the
Big Board, closed at $32.12, up 37.5 cents.